<DOC><DOCNO> AP880521-0069 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-05-21-88 0702EDT</FILEID><FIRST>r i PM-Zambia-Rebels     05-21 0197</FIRST><SECOND>PM-Zambia-Rebels,0202</SECOND><HEAD>Zambian Forces Kill 73 Mozambicans, Report Says</HEAD><DATELINE>LUSAKA, Zambia (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Security forces crossed into Mozambiqueand killed 73 guerrillas who killed peasants and stole cattle in araid on a Zambian border village, a government official was quotedas saying today.   Lusaka newspapers quoted a government spokesman as saying theguerrillas were members of the Mozambique National Resistance,which is fighting to topple Mozambique's leftist government.   The rebels were blamed for crossing into Zambia on Wednesday andraiding the village of Tafelela Nsoni in Chadiza District, killingeight peasants.   The guerrillas fled back to Mozambique with 28 stolen steers,the spokesman was quoted as saying.   Zambian security forces followed the guerrillas more than 12miles into Mozambique, attacked two rebel camps, killed 73guerrillas and recovered 22 steers, the spokesman was quoted assaying.   Mozambican rebels often cross borders to rob villages in Malawi,Zambia and Zimbabwe. As a result, Malawi and Zimbabwe have about12,000 troops stationed in Mozambique, mainly to protect supplylines vital to their landlocked economies.   Last month, President Kenneth Kaunda said Zambian forces killedseveral rebels inside his country after they attacked bordervillages and stole 150 steers.</TEXT></DOC>